      <div class="msgContentFrame">Wanted to vent.   <br /> <br />One of my cousins, the only one I'm really close to (I have a TON of cousins, dad has 12 siblings), was rear ended two days ago (I just found out this morning).  She was at a stop, and some @#%^wit rear ended her going over 70mph.  He was texting.  Her car was pushed over 100ft before they stopped and her rear bumper was resting next to the back seat (to give you an idea of the forces involved). <br /> <br />She has a broken shoulder, broken ribs, multiple internal injuries.  Sounds like she's stable, but I haven't seen her yet.  Her son was in the backseat, and now is in the ICU with a fractured spine and Lord knows what other injuries.  I want to find this guy who hit her, and if he's not already in the hospital, put him there. <br /> <br />I can't fathom why people still think they can text and drive.  When I got my first iPhone a few years ago, I finally joined the world of texting.  I figured out, on my own, very quickly that trying to do that while driving just doesn't work.  I don't even talk on my phone while driving, it's never important enough that it can't wait until I'm home or wherever I'm going.   <br /> <br />Nebraska just made texting while driving illegal, but it's a secondary offense (you can't be pulled over for it), and the way the law is implemented it's VERY hard to prove (the officer has to see the person actually holding their phone and typing on it, among other things).  Not only that, just a few days ago I saw a Lincoln police officer texting while he was driving, and very nearly swerved off the road as a result.  Even the law enforcement doesn't take it seriously. <br /> <br />I don't know where I'm going with this really, other than to express my frustration at the fact that this guy will get a slap on the wrist instead of something more serious, and will probably continue to do it.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">The greatest trick the devil ever pulled was to convince the world he didn't exist. <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/wiki/FFXIV_Windows_Gadget" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/wiki/FFXIV_Windows_Gadget">Windows 7/Vista Eorzea Gadget</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?game=268&amp;mid=128102874375645847&amp;page=1" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?game=268&amp;mid=128102874375645847&amp;page=1">Keyboard LCD Eorzea Clock</a></span> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/356033.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
