      <div class="msgContentFrame">My wife caused an accident like that a few years before I met her-- rear ended a guy while texting.  You'd think that would teach her to stop texting while driving, but it didn't.  It feels like she is texting people and/or Facebook every minute of every day.  When I'm in the car with her, and she is driving, I want to rip it out of her hands and throw it out the window.  She says she can do both just fine, and I remind her of her accident.  She says it was a fluke and won't happen again...  Yet she swerves all over the place and has almost run us into several oncoming barriers.   <br /> <br />So I offer to drive everywhere, but she says I drive too dangerously... I won't even answer my phone while driving, much less text on it.  There's just no stopping it.  <br /> <br />It's like alcohol and driving, only for a guy who hit your cousin to be going 70mph at a stop tells me he was likely more than just texting.  <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="/forum.html?forum=22&amp;mid=128504363560106769&amp;page=1" rel="external" title="ffxi.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=22&amp;mid=128504363560106769&amp;page=1">The Minecraft Thread</a></div></div>
