      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Grand Master Leatherworker ThePsychoticO wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">BrownDuck wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Grand Master Leatherworker ThePsychoticO wrote:</div><div class="orig">It's funny, the tiny risk that texting while driving causes is A HUGE, AND HORRIBLE THING THAT NEEDS TO BE BANNED. But sh*t like smoking, or alcohol take far more lives, but if someone suggested banning alcohol, they'd be called crazy.</div></div>Texting while driving is a HUGE and IMMEDIATE risk to yourself and those around you, not just in your vehicle but others nearby. Texting cannot even be compared to glancing at the speedometer or changing the radio station, because neither of those require prolonged distraction of both your eyes and your hand(s) like texting does. Even talking on the phone is less (though still somewhat) dangerous because you can still keep both eyes on the road.</div></div>Prolonged? How long does it take to read an average text? Even when you double that time, because you're looking back and forth between the road and your phone, it's still not long. Responding doesn't even require you to look at your phone. If someone can't drive with one hand, then like i've repeatedly said, they shouldn't be doing so. <br /> <br />Talking on the phone is no more dangerous than talking to someone next to you. In fact, it's potentially more dangerous, since you may look at the person next to you. Do you think talking to someone next to you while driving is too risky? Sure, it's a risk, and it definitely can distract you, but i've never heard of anyone thinking it's unacceptably risky. I wonder why that is. <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">As far as the comparison to alcohol, drunk driving IS banned practically everywhere, and carries a far heavier punishment than texting while driving. Smoking while driving has never killed anyone directly, as far as I know. I'm sure there's the odd twit who's dropped the car lighter in his crotch or flicked a cherry in his eye and had a wreck as a result, but that has more to do with being clumsy than it does with smoking.</div></div>I wasn't talking about driving. In case you missed it, i haven't been talking just about driving. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 18th 2010  3:26pm by ThePsychoticOne </span></i></div></div> <br /> <br />Do you truly believe what you are saying?  Seriously. <br /> <br />*edited to add I forgot what the original thread was about and so sorry Wint. Prayers to your cousin.  Texting while driving should be banned.  I have tried at red lights and have given up.  I have my earpiece and hate it so I don't talk on the phone...  I don't like it anyway. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 18th 2010  9:01pm by eiran </span></i></div>
